Packages
Package
Description
compiler
Defines the classes necessary to compile high-level-language code.
compiler.blocks
Defines a collection of Blocks, that are used to store the locations of instructions.
compiler.exceptions
Defines the checked Exceptions that may occur during compilation.
compiler.postfix
Defines the classes and methods necessary to: define the different Tokens that may appear in an expression convert an infix expression to its equivalent postfix expression produce the machine code that evaluates a postfix expression
compiler.symboltable
Defines a SymbolTable which is used during compilation to keep track of information about different Symbols found in a high-level-language program.
memory
A collection of interfaces that define the behaviour of a Random Access Memory object and provide additional convenience methods for reading code from RAM and writing code to RAM.
runtime
Defines the classes necessary to run machine code.
runtime.exceptions
Defines the checked Exceptions that may occur during execution.
utility
Defines utility classes.
